			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Alright, heres some information about bards...Although some songs need a wind instrument to play(Invis, etc), not many *require*.  As for charm, if you actually play a bard, you'd know a wind instrument is not going to save you after 12secs and that charm breaks.  So, you either switch to Cha increasing items in hands, or keep it at the drum.<BR>
<BR>
As for Mezzes, bards can actually Mez now, but unless its a required Mez(I am only 45th, I still have Pixie Strike), its better to have Charisma items equiped.<BR>
<BR>
That is not to say this is not a nice flute.<BR>
<BR>
Anyway, thanks to Varent, at 60th bards no longer need to have instruments thanks to a new disipline (Puretone, only with Velious).  Makes it for 2 minutes you have *the* best type of instrument no matter what youre holding.<BR>

				</font>
