				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Ok, in the hopes to clear some of this up, yes a flute (not so much this one as it has no percentage increase in song effectiveness) will increase the success of charm songs - so if you're a good little bardie and are rotating in your different instruments along with the different songs you're using, you can greatly increase your efficiency by gettin the flute in when your charm goes into effect. And as for having drum in for selo's, well then get drum in when speed song goes into effect - that's the way we're supposed to fight. Try it out, both Charm and Pixie Strike songs have much greater success rate when a magical wind instrument such as mino horn or Lyssa's Darkwood Piccolo are held in hand :). And if you're in a dungeon, playing chanter cause the party is unlucky enough to either not have one, or have chanter go LD you better be ready to step in. A wind instrument of any kind helps.
				</font>
